The paper deals with citation analysis and statistical modeling of citation data sets, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper uses data from 23 different Scopus categories, which include topics such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography (cs.CR), and cybernetics (cs.CY). Therefore, these sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
